# Bond — Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values.
All `VITE_` prefixed variables are exposed to the client bundle.

## Required for the app to run

### VITE_SUPABASE_URL
Your Supabase project URL.
Example: `https://xjrfnnmgknqsspyvrohk.supabase.co`

### VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
Your Supabase project anon (public) key.
This is safe to expose in the frontend — RLS policies protect your data.
Example: `eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...`

## Optional (for local Supabase development only — not needed for Vercel)

### SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
Server-only key with full database access. NEVER expose this in the frontend.
Used only in edge functions or server-side scripts.

### SUPABASE_DB_URL
Direct Postgres connection string. Used only for server-side database access.
Example: `postgresql://postgres:[password]@db.xjrfnnmgknqsspyvrohk.supabase.co:5432/postgres`
